<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_PrestigeAndPerks" s="488446">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0x11EF7707<!--String: "Prestige & Perks"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Perks1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d1eccaaa3661976</T>
      <T n="text">0x636E9D20<!--String: "The success and influence of a Dynasty is measured by their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Prestige</font></b>. All Members affect the Dynasty’s Prestige through their <b><font color='#199C2C'>actions</font></b>, but the actions of the Head and the Heir have a larger impact.\n\nWhen the Dynasty reaches a new <b><font color='#199C2C'>Prestige Level</font></b>, the Head is rewarded with <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty Perk Points</font></b> they can spend on <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty Perks</font></b>. While the Head is the one who picks the Perks, they affect all Members (except <b><font color='#199C2C'>Outcasts</font></b>).\n\nDynasties can <b><font color='#199C2C'>lose</font></b> Prestige Levels if their members behave poorly. Then the Perk Points and Perks gained from the last Level increase will be lost."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Perks2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d1eccaaa3661975</T>
      <T n="text">0x236191A3<!--String: "Prestige is <b><font color='#199C2C'>increased</font></b> by:\n• Doing Activities Encouraged by Dynasty Values\n• Going to work in Careers Encouraged by Dynasty Values \n• Going to school with Good Grades\n• Making new Friends and Good Friends\n• Hosting group Social Events \n• Marrying Members of other Dynasties \n• Starting Alliances & Rivalries\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Higher</font></b> Career Levels, Grades, and Social Event Scores <b><font color='#199C2C'>give more Prestige</font></b>. When marrying or starting an Alliance or Rivalry, the Prestige reward gets bigger the higher the <b><font color='#199C2C'>other Dynasty’s Prestige Level</font></b> is. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Perks3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d1eccaaa3661974</T>
      <T n="text">0xC6191ABF<!--String: "Prestige is <b><font color='#199C2C'>decreased</font></b> by:\n• Doing Activities Discouraged by Dynasty Values \n• Going to work in Careers Discouraged by Dynasty Values\n• Ending Alliances & Rivalries\n• Scandals being revealed\n\nPrestige will also decrease gradually over time, unless this is turned off in Pack Settings.\n\nHigher levels in <b><font color='#199C2C'>Discouraged Careers</font></b> and more Severe Scandals lead to <b><font color='#199C2C'>greater Prestige loss</font></b>. When a Rivalry or Alliance ends, the Prestige penalty is proportional to the <b><font color='#199C2C'>other Dynasty’s Prestige Level</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Perks4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5d1eccaaa3661973</T>
      <T n="text">0xDDB00C74<!--String: "Every time the Prestige Level increases, the Dynasty Head can purchase additional <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty Perks</font></b> via the Dynasty panel! Some Perks have a Prestige Level <b><font color='#199C2C'>requirement</font></b>, as well. Many Perks have <b><font color='#199C2C'>three levels</font></b> of increasingly stronger bonuses.\n\nThere is a special type of Perk called <b><font color='#199C2C'>Inheritable Traits</font></b>. These Perks give <b><font color='#199C2C'>babies born to Dynasty Members</font></b> a chance to get special <b><font color='#199C2C'>Affinity Traits</font></b>, which in turn can be <b><font color='#199C2C'>inherited</font></b> by their children. These Traits grow <b><font color='#199C2C'>stronger over the generations</font></b> until they reach the third and final level.\n"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
